This doughnut, toasted cinnamon ice cream sandwich recipe is for people who have a sweet tooth but are far too lazy to recreate their desserts from scratch.  This recipe makes use of store bought doughnuts, as well as store bought ice cream, and is super quick and easy to make.  Enjoy these ice cream sandwiches as a midday snack, or as dessert after dinner tonight.  We have also added an ice cream sandwich recipe for the cooks and bakers who love to make their own dessert components and recreate their recipes from scratch. ALSO TRY: Recipe of the day: No-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies This recipe was found on delicious.com.au This recipe was found on thebakermama.com